in search of a bride.

19:56.154 --> 20:00.367
- You understand that, cowboy?
- Yeah.

20:01.952 --> 20:04.288
What are ya doin'?

20:05.789 --> 20:08.000
- These are my shoes.
- Oh, yeah.

20:08.167 --> 20:10.794
- And these are my legs.
- Yeah.

20:10.961 --> 20:16.008
- What are you gonna do with them?
- With the shoes or the legs?

20:16.175 --> 20:19.761
Last time I saw legs like that,
they had a message tied to 'em.

20:19.928 --> 20:24.725
What do you mean? These are
great little legs. I'm a professional.

20:25.893 --> 20:30.397
Well, in that case,
you shouldn't be dressed in white.

20:30.564 --> 20:33.525
- Dancer.
- Oh.

20:35.277 --> 20:38.197
Well, cowboys love fat calves.

20:39.281 --> 20:42.743
- They're not fat.
- They're bigger than mine.

20:42.910 --> 20:46.705
- Do we really wanna talk about legs?
- One of us does.

20:46.872 --> 20:52.836
Otherwise we wouldn't have gone...
What are we doing now?

20:53.003 --> 20:56.632
Well, I am getting my clothes, you fool.

20:57.466 --> 21:00.636
Good idea. Why don't you
slip into somethin' comfortable?

21:03.889 --> 21:07.684
Are we really going 110?
We're going 110!

21:07.851 --> 21:11.897
Why do you wear that cowboy hat?
Because you think it looks dazzling on you.

21:13.148 --> 21:15.692
I'd no idea this dress
would be so hard to get out of.

22:05.450 --> 22:07.536
Hold up on that car wash, gentlemen.

22:11.039 --> 22:13.500
Come here, son.

22:15.878 --> 22:17.796
Whoops!

22:19.923 --> 22:23.218
You look tired, boy. Rest yourself.

22:25.804 --> 22:29.850
You punks look tuckered out, too.

22:35.230 --> 22:37.941
That's an attention-getter.

22:38.775 --> 22:42.863
- Now, a lady in a weddin' gown.
- Yes, sir.

22:43.864 --> 22:46.617
- Get in a car?
- Yes, sir.

22:46.783 --> 22:49.912
- See who was drivin'?
- N-no, sir.

22:52.289 --> 22:56.710
- Licence plate?
- Y-yes, sir. Georgia plates.

22:56.877 --> 22:58.670
"Ban-one. "

22:58.837 --> 23:03.342
B- A-N dash O-N-E.

23:03.509 --> 23:07.596
All right. Now, you boys
just stay here and watch the car.

23:07.763 --> 23:11.016
There might be some vandals around
who wanna steal somethin',

23:11.183 --> 23:14.394
so you boys just stay here
and keep your hands on the car

23:14.561 --> 23:18.273
until one of my associates arrive.

23:18.440 --> 23:25.155
And don't go home, don't go to eat,
and don't play with yourself.

23:25.322 --> 23:28.492
It wouldn't look nice on my highway.

23:28.659 --> 23:34.915
Oh, you can think about it,
but don't do it.

23:49.930 --> 23:52.599
Hey, man, he's gone.
Let's get outta here.

23:52.766 --> 23:56.812
Shit! You do what you want.
I'm stayin' right here.

24:00.899 --> 24:05.070
28 years old and... Oh, goodness,
what's this? I'll tuck it right in.

24:05.237 --> 24:08.699
I was down here dancing
in a home appliance show.

24:08.866 --> 24:11.952
<i>- I danced around three trash mashers.
- Talk to me, my boy.</i>

24:12.119 --> 24:16.165
I had this costume that lit up.
I only short-circuited once.

24:16.331 --> 24:20.919
- Where did you get that seat cover, son?
- This ain't no seat cover.

24:21.086 --> 24:24.756
- I was standing in the parking lot...
- I'm sitting next to Lawrence of Arabia.

24:24.923 --> 24:29.636
I met this guy... These can't be my pants.
God, he was good-looking.

24:29.803 --> 24:32.181
- And he had this hat on...
- Funny, ain't she?

24:32.347 --> 24:37.436
I think he was from Texas or something,
and I thought, "Why not marry the guy?"

24:41.064 --> 24:44.610
Nobody walks out
on a pretty weddin' I set up.

24:44.776 --> 24:47.404
I'm gonna get that girl
and set everything straight.

24:47.571 --> 24:53.160
She insulted my town.
She insulted my son.

24:55.287 --> 24:59.500
- Look, what if we...
- Shut up! She insulted my authority.

25:00.876 --> 25:06.465
And that's nothin' but pure and simple
old-fashioned Communism.

25:06.632 --> 25:10.177
It happens every time one of those
dancers starts poontangin' around...

25:10.344 --> 25:12.429
with those show-folk fags.

25:12.596 --> 25:15.349
Halfway down the aisle I said to myself,

25:15.516 --> 25:18.101
"Jesus Christ, what are you doing?
His mother doesn't even have any teeth!"

25:18.268 --> 25:21.396
I jumped in this car, and it blew up
on the side of the road,

25:21.563 --> 25:24.733
and I ended up in this goddamn airplane.
What do you do?

25:25.400 --> 25:28.028
I don't remember.

25:28.195 --> 25:32.699
- Oh, are we on the air?
- Sort of, yeah.

25:34.201 --> 25:37.830
You think I'm... nuts, don't you?

25:37.996 --> 25:40.415
No, I don't think you're crazy.

25:40.582 --> 25:45.128
I picked up three brides yesterday,
just like you, very subdued.

25:45.295 --> 25:48.590
Hey, what... what's goin' on up there?

25:49.007 --> 25:51.677
<i>- Come back, Bandit.
- Bandit?</i>

25:51.844 --> 25:57.850
- Is that your name or your profession?
- That's my handle. Bo's my real name.

25:58.016 --> 26:00.519
- What's your name?
- Carrie.

26:00.686 --> 26:04.356
Is she wearing a wedding dress?

26:07.025 --> 26:08.402
She was.

26:08.569 --> 26:12.155
What's she wearin' now?
Come back.

26:12.322 --> 26:15.242
Hey, you got peanut butter
or somethin' in your ears?

26:15.409 --> 26:19.705
Tell me what that woman's got on...
her mind!

26:20.539 --> 26:21.915
10-4!

26:22.082 --> 26:26.003
No coozie's gonna leave me
at no church.

26:26.170 --> 26:29.840
Decoratin' up a whole town
at a cost of $40.

26:30.007 --> 26:32.551
Right.

26:33.760 --> 26:39.558
I can see her now,
runnin' back up that aisle...

26:39.725 --> 26:43.020
No, she was dancin'
back up the aisle,

26:43.187 --> 26:46.148
her knockers bouncin'
all over the joint.

26:47.024 --> 26:49.443
Let go of that wheel.

26:50.652 --> 26:53.488
Why, her ass was wigglin', too.

26:58.160 --> 27:01.830
Why so fast?
You're late for a big bowling date?

27:01.997 --> 27:03.540
Cute.

27:06.210 --> 27:11.131
- So, tell me about yourself.
- What do you wanna know, my sign?

27:11.298 --> 27:15.344
- What do you do besides drive fast?
- Have fun.

27:15.511 --> 27:18.889
- Is this fun?
- Drivin'?

27:19.056 --> 27:23.936
- Driving, talking to me.
- They're both a challenge.

27:25.646 --> 27:30.442
- You've got a great profile.
- Yeah, don't I? Especially from the side.

27:31.109 --> 27:33.487
At least we finally agree on something.

27:33.654 --> 27:37.074
Yeah. We both like half my face.

27:42.996 --> 27:46.583
Hey, would a cop taking a leak
on the side of the road interest you?

27:48.043 --> 27:50.420
Yes, it would.

27:50.587 --> 27:56.385
- He's taking a 10-100.
- At least it's better than a 10-200.

28:00.597 --> 28:02.516
- Smokey.
- Smokey.

28:28.000 --> 28:31.879
- Is this fun?
- I forgot to tell ya:

28:32.045 --> 28:35.424
I'm runnin' blocker for 400 cases
of illegal Coors.

28:52.024 --> 28:53.859
Holy shit!

28:56.153 --> 29:00.032
I don't believe this.
Funny, I don't remember that turn.

29:00.199 --> 29:04.495
<i>- Bandit, where the hell are you?
- I'll be back on the highway in a second.</i>

29:04.661 --> 29:06.914
<i>All right, good buddy.
I'll keep my eyes peeled.</i>

29:20.802 --> 29:24.681
- Them things are fabulous.
- I think I just went 10-100.

29:24.848 --> 29:29.061
- Well, it's better than 10-200.
- That's true.

29:36.193 --> 29:40.239
<i># Well, the more wheels I got
the better I like it.</i>

29:40.405 --> 29:44.660
<i># I'm the brother of a truck-driving mother
boogity, boogity, boogity, boogity. #</i>

29:48.914 --> 29:52.376
- Snowman, you got your ears on?
- You lucky devil, you got him.

29:52.543 --> 29:55.963
- Where the hell are you?
- I'm on a two-lane blacktop.

29:56.129 --> 30:00.676
Highway marker number 71.
How's our time doin'?

30:01.677 --> 30:06.974
Oh, how are we doin' on time?
About 25 minutes ahead of schedule.

30:07.140 --> 30:11.144
- What's your 20?
- I'm about four miles ahead of you, turkey.

30:11.311 --> 30:12.813
Not for long.

30:12.980 --> 30:18.151
<i>- Breaker to the Bandit.
- Come on back, breaker.</i>

30:18.694 --> 30:22.239
<i>Bandit, I've got a smokey report
for you. Come on.</i>

30:22.406 --> 30:26.243
<i>- Well, talk to me, good buddy.
- You've got trouble comin'.</i>

30:26.410 --> 30:29.955
Well, what's your handle, son,
and, uh, what's your 20?

30:30.122 --> 30:36.128
<i>My handle's Smokey Bear,
and I'm tail-grabbin'your ass right now.</i>

30:38.630 --> 30:43.135
Goddamn. That's a Texas mountie.
What the hell's he doin' in Arkansas?

30:43.302 --> 30:47.014
Well, let's just see what
he's got under the hood.

30:47.181 --> 30:48.891
Bye-bye, baby!

31:02.362 --> 31:04.740
You smoke much?

31:04.907 --> 31:07.326
I just started.

31:10.787 --> 31:15.167
<i>- Cledus, you got your ears on, son?
- Oh, bring it on, you lucky devil.</i>

31:15.334 --> 31:17.503
- Comin' around you.
- Be careful.

31:17.669 --> 31:21.340
You're gonna have to make your own lane,
'cause you definitely got oncoming traffic.

31:21.507 --> 31:22.883
Be careful. Be careful.

31:30.265 --> 31:32.893
Oh, my... Oh, my God!

31:33.060 --> 31:36.939
I'm about to be killed in this...
in this moving CB radio show,

31:37.105 --> 31:40.734
and I... I don't even have a handle!

31:41.360 --> 31:45.614
You want a handle?
OK, I'll think one up for ya. Let's see.

31:45.781 --> 31:48.075
- Oh, I got one for ya!
- What?

31:50.577 --> 31:52.663
Just give me a minute here.

31:54.373 --> 31:56.416
He done good, didn't he, Fred?

32:02.047 --> 32:03.882
What?

32:04.049 --> 32:05.759
Frog.

32:06.969 --> 32:10.097
- Why?
- 'Cause you're always hoppin' around.

32:10.264 --> 32:14.726
And you're kinda cute like a frog,
and... I'd like to jump ya.

32:17.896 --> 32:19.857
Nobody...

32:20.023 --> 32:25.237
Nobody makes Sheriff Buford T. Justice
look like a possum's pecker.

32:25.404 --> 32:28.532
- Except for that...
- Shut your ass.

32:32.619 --> 32:36.373
- Break for that, Bandit One.
- Yeah, Snowman, come on back.

32:36.540 --> 32:38.876
That was a Texas bubblegum machine
on your back door.

32:39.042 --> 32:42.629
- A Texas bubblegum machine?
- Yeah, I saw him.

32:54.933 --> 32:59.605
You ain't gonna believe this, but that crazy
sombitch tried to drive up under my truck.

32:59.771 --> 33:02.733
What's a Texas county mountie
doing in Arkansas?

33:02.900 --> 33:05.569
<i>- I don't know.
- I don't know.</i>

33:05.736 --> 33:08.030
I don't know!

33:08.197 --> 33:12.034
- Well, who the hell knows?
- I really don't know.

33:14.411 --> 33:20.918
What we're dealin' with here is
a complete lack of respect for the law.

33:21.752 --> 33:25.506
<i>This is Sheriff Buford T. Justice.</i>

33:25.672 --> 33:29.009
<i>I'm in pursuit of a black TransAm.</i>

33:29.176 --> 33:33.722
<i>He's all mine, so stay outta the way.</i>

33:42.105 --> 33:45.317
This is Sheriff George Branford
of Deeson County, Arkansas.

33:45.484 --> 33:48.737
We are apprised of the situation
and are taking appropriate measures.

33:48.904 --> 33:50.489
Did you say you are a sheriff?

33:50.656 --> 33:54.034
That's a big 10-4!

33:54.201 --> 33:58.080
This is Sheriff Buford T. Justice
of Texas!

33:58.247 --> 34:01.834
Texas? You know, of course,
that you're out of your jurisdiction.

34:02.000 --> 34:04.419
I suggest that you let my department
handle the situation.

34:04.586 --> 34:09.382
That's very comfortin',
but I'm in a high-speed pursuit.

34:09.550 --> 34:12.386
- Don't you hear good?
- I hear perfectly.

34:12.553 --> 34:15.222
The fact that you are a sheriff
is not germane to the situation.

34:15.389 --> 34:19.101
The goddamn Germans
got nothin' to do with it!

34:19.268 --> 34:21.311
- What?
- Shut up! One shit at a time!

34:27.609 --> 34:31.989
- What do ya see?
- We lost him.

34:39.913 --> 34:43.083
This is Sheriff Buford T. Justice again.

34:43.250 --> 34:46.712
I lost that TransAm.
Set up a roadblock.

34:46.879 --> 34:49.590
- Good idea!
- What the hell you know?

34:49.755 --> 34:52.801
I believe we have the situation
well under control, Sheriff.

34:57.014 --> 34:59.725
<i>Breaker, breaker, lookin' for the Bandit.</i>

34:59.892 --> 35:02.811
<i>- You out there, son?
- You got the Bandit. Come on back.</i>

35:02.978 --> 35:08.317
My handle's Silver-Tongued Devil. Your fellow
CBers are mighty proud of ya out there.

35:08.483 --> 35:10.486
Thank ya, son. I appreciate it.

35:10.652 --> 35:14.072
Tell me, you comin' up
on Fayetteville and Interstate 82?

35:14.239 --> 35:18.619
- We're almost on top of it.
- I got a big bad bear story for you there.

35:18.785 --> 35:21.455
I just rolled past
a county mountie roadblock.

35:21.622 --> 35:26.543
- You ARE a silver-tongued devil.
- That's a big 10-4, good buddy.

35:26.710 --> 35:31.548
Well, you keep your wheels spinnin'
and the beavers grinnin', then. I'm out.

35:31.715 --> 35:34.259
Why, thank you, Officer.

35:34.426 --> 35:36.887
- Classy guy.
- Classy guy.

36:00.577 --> 36:03.580
Did you see that? They went
right through our roadblock.

36:03.747 --> 36:06.375
You sombitches couldn't
close an umbrella.

36:36.321 --> 36:40.826
You know somethin', Sheriff? If J.W.
Don't get out of my way, I'll pass him.

36:40.993 --> 36:43.579
Where? In the woods?

36:43.745 --> 36:48.500
I don't care if your daddy is the mayor.
You wreck this car, it'll come outta your pay.

36:49.251 --> 36:52.754
- Yeah, but he's gettin' away.
- Son, he's not goin' anywhere.

36:52.921 --> 36:56.300
The Mulberry Bridge has been dismantled
for the past six months.

37:02.472 --> 37:04.725
That's not good.

37:09.688 --> 37:12.065
It would be better with a whole bridge.

37:13.233 --> 37:15.652
And that's worse.

37:18.989 --> 37:23.035
- Why don't you drop me off? I'll catch a cab.
- Too late now.

37:35.339 --> 37:37.216
We did it! We did it!

37:48.268 --> 37:50.354
See? I didn't wreck it, Sheriff.

37:53.524 --> 37:55.359
We jumped over that bridge!

37:55.526 --> 37:58.362
- Did you see what we did?
- Yes, I did.

37:58.529 --> 38:02.449
I wanna jump something else! I wanna
jump a house! I wanna jump something!

38:02.616 --> 38:04.618
Well, jump me.

38:06.912 --> 38:11.625
- Honest to God, it wasn't my fault! I stopped!
- Yeah, right.

38:11.792 --> 38:15.379
Hey, boy, where's Sheriff Branford?

38:16.296 --> 38:19.550
<i>I am Sheriff Branford.</i>

38:20.843 --> 38:25.097
Oh, hey...
For some reason or another,

38:25.264 --> 38:29.685
you sounded a little taller on radio.

38:34.439 --> 38:38.735
What the hell is
the world comin' to?

38:46.910 --> 38:50.330
<i>Sounds good to me,
Tower of Power. Listen, buddy...</i>

38:50.497 --> 38:52.958
- What channel we on?
- What?

38:53.125 --> 38:57.129
- What channel are we on?
- 11.

38:58.130 --> 38:59.756
Snowman, are you out there?

38:59.923 --> 39:04.344
I'm doin' what I'm supposed to be doin'.
What are y'all doing, he'n' and she'n'?

39:04.511 --> 39:07.264
- Come back.
- Oh, we were playin' a little bridge.

39:07.431 --> 39:12.394
- How we been doin'?
- We're losin' minutes, son.

39:12.561 --> 39:18.025
If you don't get up here and run me some
interference, we ain't never gonna make it.

39:18.192 --> 39:23.030
I'll drop the dolly off at a choke-and-puke,
and then I'll get right back on the job.

39:23.197 --> 39:26.200
All right.
10-4 on that choke-and-puke.

39:26.366 --> 39:29.203
<i>- Oh, by the way, Bandit...
- Yeah, guy?</i>

39:29.369 --> 39:32.998
How 'bout bringin' me a hamburger for Fred?
I'm beginnin' to worry about him.

39:33.165 --> 39:36.084
<i>- He's lookin' a little thin in the skin.
- You got 'em.</i>

39:36.251 --> 39:39.922
- Choke-and-puke.
- Choke-and-puke.

39:40.088 --> 39:43.759
- That's where I'll get off?
- Right.

39:46.845 --> 39:49.348
You oughta give up smokin'.
That's bad for your health.

39:49.515 --> 39:52.601
But I enjoy it so much.

40:09.117 --> 40:13.539
I guess you can get
your ticket over there.

40:13.956 --> 40:16.083
- You got enough money?
- Yeah.

40:16.250 --> 40:20.254
I have enough to get to Jersey,
walk the rest of the way.

40:22.422 --> 40:27.386
- Hey, thanks.
- Oh, it was nothing.

40:28.762 --> 40:31.765
- I'll see you around.
- Yeah.

40:34.935 --> 40:37.229
Frog?

40:39.314 --> 40:41.066
You gonna be all right?

40:46.655 --> 40:50.659
Yeah... I'm always all right.

41:03.213 --> 41:07.259
Can I have a couple of cheeseburgers
to go and a glass of iced tea?

41:15.601 --> 41:18.312
How much I owe ya, ma'am?

41:18.478 --> 41:20.939
- A dollar and a half.
- Keep the change.

41:21.106 --> 41:25.486
Just keep your eye out
for that Mr Bandit bastard!

41:27.863 --> 41:33.994
Let me have a diablo sandwich, a Dr Pepper.
Make it fast. I'm in a goddamn hurry.

41:34.161 --> 41:36.872
- You want somethin'?
- A hush puppy, Daddy.

41:37.039 --> 41:42.336
We got no time for that crap!
Dumb sombitch!

41:43.337 --> 41:46.590
- Diablo and Doc.
- Thank you, nice lady.

41:46.757 --> 41:50.886
- You must be in a hell of a hurry, Sheriff?
- You bet your ass on that, boy.

41:51.053 --> 41:56.141
Oh, you got a little mess there.
Let me help you get that off there...

41:56.308 --> 41:59.686
- Yeah, yeah. Much obliged.
- Yeah.

41:59.853 --> 42:02.773
Who ya chasin'?
Somebody chasin' you?

42:02.940 --> 42:04.650
Nobody chasin' me, boy.

42:04.817 --> 42:10.280
I been chasin' a goddamn maniac
all the way from Texarkana, Texas.

42:10.447 --> 42:13.575
Really?
What is he, a bank robber?

42:13.742 --> 42:16.370
Bank robber?

42:16.537 --> 42:21.583
Bank robbin' is baby shit
alongside of what this dude is doin'.

42:22.751 --> 42:24.920
Almost killed 20 law officers.

42:25.087 --> 42:28.966
Drivin' through people's backyards,
knockin' down mailboxes.

42:29.132 --> 42:32.594
He's got a broad in the car,
took her across the state line.

42:32.761 --> 42:35.055
That's the Mann Act.

42:35.222 --> 42:38.559
I don't think he's got her permission,
and that's kidnapping.

42:38.725 --> 42:41.562
- How's that for high jinks?
- Yeah.

42:43.939 --> 42:46.400
- What I owe?
- Oh, let me pay for it.

42:46.567 --> 42:49.987
- You're an officer of the law. I'd be honoured.
- Much obliged.

42:50.154 --> 42:53.657
- Where's the can? I gotta take a squirt.
- Right back there. Just used it.

42:59.163 --> 43:02.332
Hey! Hey!
What are you doin' in my car?

43:02.499 --> 43:05.127
- You're goin' the wrong way!
- Oh.

43:05.711 --> 43:07.588
- Hang on!
- What the hell are ya doin'?

43:07.754 --> 43:10.841
- Sheriff Justice is in there!
- I know! I know!

43:18.724 --> 43:21.351
- Thank you, nice lady.
- Sure thing.

43:27.065 --> 43:29.067
Yoo-hoo! Sheriff!

43:33.780 --> 43:35.574
Oh, boy.

43:37.784 --> 43:40.204
Nice ass.

43:47.461 --> 43:50.088
I didn't want to be dumped
at any old truck stop.

43:50.255 --> 43:54.343
- I wanted to stay with you.
- Well, why didn't you ask?

43:54.510 --> 43:58.514
You might've said no, and I have
a hard time handling rejections.

44:41.473 --> 44:44.518
We're gainin' on 'em.

44:44.685 --> 44:48.313
I think it'd be a good idea
if we changed places, don't you?

44:48.480 --> 44:52.317
You be a passenger for a while now.
Up, up... I'll just slide right...

44:52.484 --> 44:55.487
- Oh, you got my hair.
- Sorry. I'll slide right under.

44:55.654 --> 44:58.824
- Ooh, I don't know. Wait. Wait. Wait!
- I got it. I got it!

44:58.991 --> 45:00.367
- Wait a minute!
- Wait a minute!

45:00.534 --> 45:02.995
Hold it! I'm stuck here.
This is not workin'.

45:03.162 --> 45:07.291
- I got my foot on the...
- Goddamn it! I seen it in the movies!

45:17.342 --> 45:19.970
Oh, my God!

45:20.596 --> 45:24.474
Duck, or you're gonna
be talkin' outta your ass!

45:31.231 --> 45:35.819
- Daddy, the top came off.
- No shit

45:43.327 --> 45:45.871
Snowman! How are your vocal cords?

45:46.038 --> 45:50.709
Well, my vocal cords are fine.
I'm a little worried about Fred now.

45:50.876 --> 45:56.256
He's been gnawing everything, barkin' and
screamin'. He's turned into a stalk of bananas.

45:56.423 --> 46:00.344
- What's your 20?
- About 16 miles this side of Mississippi.

46:00.511 --> 46:04.515
Whoa, hold it. I just passed
another Kojak with a Kodak.

46:04.681 --> 46:08.769
This place is crawlin' with bears.
Where the hell are you? Come back.

46:08.936 --> 46:14.149
I'm still tryin' to get rid of that Texas County
mountie. I don't know what the hell he wants.

46:14.316 --> 46:19.196
You know what he wants. How would you like
to be the dude that handcuffs a legend?

46:19.363 --> 46:24.576
Give me five minutes, we'll put some moves
on that mother. I'll meet ya at Old Miss.

46:24.743 --> 46:27.996
You'd better hurry, or we can just kiss
that money goodbye. Understand?

46:28.163 --> 46:30.499
I read you loud and clear. 10-4.

46:30.666 --> 46:34.628
You got the one Snowman.
I'm eastbound and down.

46:34.795 --> 46:37.589
We gone, killer.

46:48.225 --> 46:51.520
That's the way I wanna go out.
Hey, man, watch it!

46:54.940 --> 46:58.152
- What the hell was that?
- A left, or half a 'u'.

46:58.318 --> 47:00.946
Well, please don't do it anymore.

47:03.407 --> 47:07.452
Hey, you know who that was?
Check this out.

47:07.619 --> 47:10.164
Bandit, this here's the Grave Robber.

47:10.330 --> 47:15.294
Put the pedal to the metal, and we'll hold
this county mountie as long as we can.

47:15.460 --> 47:18.046
- Well, go, girl, go!
- I'm goin'! I'm goin'!

47:18.213 --> 47:21.258
I've got the metal to the pedal,
and the thing to the floor...

47:49.369 --> 47:51.705
Damn, he had a lot of friends, didn't he?

47:51.872 --> 47:54.583
If they had cremated the son of a bitch,

47:54.750 --> 47:59.963
I could've been kickin' that Mr Bandit's
ass around the moon by now.

48:15.479 --> 48:17.731
Hold my hat!

48:17.898 --> 48:21.276
- My hat blew off, Daddy.
- I hope your goddamn head was in it.

48:24.655 --> 48:27.241
- OK. We're gonna switch.
- OK.

48:27.407 --> 48:31.411
I'm comin' over underneath you.
You just slide right on over.

48:31.662 --> 48:34.164
I think I'm in love with your belt buckle.

48:38.836 --> 48:41.588
Close. Colourful, but close.

48:51.849 --> 48:54.935
I like this seat better anyway.

48:55.102 --> 48:57.688
Yes, have a smoke. It seems to help.

48:58.605 --> 49:00.524
Come on, defence!

49:02.109 --> 49:03.777
Come on, Billy Ray, get tough!

49:03.944 --> 49:07.281
You know, I wanted to be
a high-fashion model once.

49:07.447 --> 49:12.578
But, hell, how long can you
model clothes for 8-year-olds? Boys.

49:12.744 --> 49:16.832
Besides that, my cheeks were too fat.
These cheeks, these.

49:18.584 --> 49:21.086
Aarghhh!

49:22.004 --> 49:25.382
- Oh, my goodness, we're airborne here.
- Jesus Christ!

49:25.549 --> 49:30.179
- Oh, look, a football game!
- There's kids! For Christ's sake, watch out!

49:30.345 --> 49:34.057
- Don't hit the kids!
- Get your hands off my wheel!

49:34.224 --> 49:36.768
Lean to the left, lean to the right...

49:47.696 --> 49:52.367
Stand up there and see if you can see
where the hell they went.

49:53.035 --> 49:57.498
- Can you see anything?
- It's a football game. Can we watch, Daddy?

49:57.664 --> 50:01.168
- You stay and watch. I'm goin' back!
- But, Daddy...

50:07.591 --> 50:11.553
<i># Bandit, you're reckless
and you live much too hard #</i>

50:11.720 --> 50:14.473
Oughta be in Nashville.

50:14.640 --> 50:18.185
<i>Snowman, are ya out there, son?
What's your 20? Where are you?</i>

50:19.311 --> 50:23.440
I'm at mile marker 85. Come back.

50:23.607 --> 50:26.527
<i>Son-of-a-gun! So am I!</i>

50:29.863 --> 50:34.284
Well, damned if ya ain't.
Damned if ya ain't.

50:54.179 --> 50:56.390
Cledus... This is Frog.

50:56.557 --> 50:59.309
Hello, Frog. I want you
to meet Fred, Frog.

50:59.476 --> 51:02.980
- This is for Fred.
- Frog, feed Fred.

51:03.147 --> 51:05.691
What's wrong with you? You were gonna
dump the chick at the truck stop.

51:05.858 --> 51:09.987
- I ran into complications.
- You always run into complications.

51:10.154 --> 51:13.323
Always the same, some chick.
We ain't doin' good time.

51:13.490 --> 51:17.035
- What are we yappin' for?
- It's the chick.

51:19.746 --> 51:22.916
- Switch down to the next channel, right?
- Yeah.

51:24.084 --> 51:27.171
Hey, Bandit? Nice ass.

51:27.337 --> 51:29.756
- Thanks a lot.
- Thanks a lot.

51:39.308 --> 51:43.979
All right, Fred. Come on.
Let's go, boy. Come on.

51:44.146 --> 51:46.482
Fred, I'm tired of pickin' you up... Fred!

51:50.235 --> 51:54.156
- Did Cledus call you a legend?
- Uh-huh.

51:54.990 --> 52:00.078
- Why?
- Well, I used to do some crazy things.

52:00.245 --> 52:02.206
- I used to.
- Oh.

52:06.001 --> 52:07.461
So did I.

52:07.628 --> 52:12.674
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

52:12.841 --> 52:15.427
One, two... I'm a gypsy... four.

52:15.594 --> 52:20.182
That's someone who goes from chorus line
to chorus line... six, seven, eight.

52:22.226 --> 52:26.980
- You know, I was on Broadway once.
- Really?

52:27.147 --> 52:29.858
- For almost 12 minutes.
- Oh.

52:30.025 --> 52:32.569
The show closed the first night.

52:32.736 --> 52:38.617
But, God, I was so good. You shoulda
seen me. You'd have loved me.

52:44.832 --> 52:48.794
What do you do? Straight.

52:52.673 --> 52:58.220
I just go from place to place
and... do what I do best.

52:59.012 --> 53:02.182
- What's that?
- Show off.

53:06.228 --> 53:09.481
Yeah. You do do that well.

53:12.776 --> 53:14.778
You do.

53:15.988 --> 53:18.949
So do I.
Five, six, seven, eight.

53:19.116 --> 53:22.995
- For almost 12 minutes.
- Oh, shut up!

53:25.581 --> 53:30.127
Come here, Fred. Come here, boy.
Fred, don't you make me come after you.

53:30.878 --> 53:34.590
Get over here, Fred! Come here.

53:34.756 --> 53:39.636
I'm in a hurry, and you want to swim.
You're drivin' me crazy, Fred.

53:43.682 --> 53:49.771
What is the matter with you, Fred?
That's it for you and the truck drivin'!

53:58.238 --> 54:01.658
Look, I've got to go 10-100.
Could I have a dime?

54:01.825 --> 54:05.537
- Crawl under.
- Terrific.

54:05.704 --> 54:08.165
"Crawl under. "

54:15.005 --> 54:18.967
- TransAm! What's your pleasure?
- Fill it up, my man.

54:20.302 --> 54:22.638
Gimme that talker.

54:25.390 --> 54:28.227
Hello? Mr Bandit?

54:29.269 --> 54:32.189
<i>Would you just happen
to be listenin' out there?</i>

54:32.356 --> 54:34.107
Can you hear me, boy?

54:36.443 --> 54:38.904
This is the Bandit.
Who've I got at that end?

54:39.655 --> 54:42.991
This is Sheriff Buford T. Justice
of Texas.

54:43.158 --> 54:46.578
Well, hot damn.
Welcome to Mississippi, Sheriff.

54:46.745 --> 54:48.372
Thank you, Mr Bandit.

54:48.539 --> 54:53.210
And I got a big welcome waitin' for you
when I get you back home,

54:53.377 --> 54:55.170
you sombitch!

54:55.337 --> 54:57.381
Don't you cuss
on this here radio.

54:57.548 --> 55:02.261
I apologise to all the friendly folk
who are listenin'.

55:02.427 --> 55:06.974
Now hear this, you tick turd:
I'm gonna get you.

55:07.140 --> 55:12.020
I didn't come all the way this far
to go home with empty pockets.

55:12.187 --> 55:15.649
I been meanin' to ask you that.
How come you're followin' me?

55:15.816 --> 55:19.444
I'd be delighted to tell you, Mr Bandit.

55:19.611 --> 55:24.116
You see, when I get you back home,

55:24.283 --> 55:28.162
I'm gonna find the tallest tree
in the country,

55:28.328 --> 55:33.041
<i>and then I'm gonna hang you from it.</i>

55:33.208 --> 55:35.752
- Sheriff?
- I'm listenin'.

55:35.919 --> 55:38.714
Do the letters F.O.
Mean anything to you?

55:42.593 --> 55:45.012
Smart aleck.

55:47.097 --> 55:49.433
You keep this one for yourself.

55:49.600 --> 55:54.396
- Have a smooth ride, Mr Bandit.
- Thank you, partner.

55:58.901 --> 56:00.652
Oof!

56:05.407 --> 56:07.117
<i>Snowman, I'm right beside you.</i>

56:07.284 --> 56:10.329
<i>Looks like we got a clear shot
all the way to the 'Bama state line.</i>

56:10.496 --> 56:15.209
<i>Oh, a clear shot?
I'm gonna believe that when I see it.</i>

56:15.375 --> 56:20.214
This is Sheriff Buford T. Justice
puttin' out an all-point advisory.

56:20.380 --> 56:25.427
<i>That black TransAm is now
headed toward Alabama.</i>

56:26.261 --> 56:28.889
What happened, Daddy?

56:29.056 --> 56:32.142
Get back in the goddamn car.

56:36.188 --> 56:40.275
You know who I feel has revolutionised
the American musical theatre?

56:40.442 --> 56:43.403
- Stephen Sondheim.
- Yeah?

56:43.570 --> 56:46.240
- Who's that?
- Stephen Sondheim?

56:46.406 --> 56:49.326
- Does he do a lot of musicals and stuff?
- Yeah.

56:49.493 --> 56:52.663
- He ever do anything with Brenda Lee?
- Does she dance?

56:52.830 --> 56:56.667
- She spins. She's a little spinner.
- Oh, they were a good group.

56:56.834 --> 56:58.836
- The Spinners were good. Yeah.
- Yeah.

56:59.002 --> 57:01.213
Have you ever been in any plays?

57:01.380 --> 57:05.175
Holy shit. We got
a lot of company up there.

57:05.342 --> 57:07.386
A lot of company.

57:07.553 --> 57:10.889
- Sarge, here he comes.
- Yeah, I got eyes.

57:23.026 --> 57:26.905
- Are you ready, Roy?
- I was born ready.

57:27.072 --> 57:29.158
Don't just stand there. Go get him!

57:29.324 --> 57:33.871
- Drives pretty good, don't he, Sarge?
- We'll see about that.

57:51.972 --> 57:55.851
- Sarge, you OK?
- You see me movin', don't ya?

58:16.288 --> 58:20.792
- Wanna do a little pond hopping, Frog?
- Uh... Swell.

59:30.821 --> 59:33.740
Now, I know you're
in a little distress here,

59:33.907 --> 59:36.869
but did you see
a black TransAm go by?

59:37.035 --> 59:40.122
He caused all of this, the Bandit.
Ain't he somethin'?

59:41.748 --> 59:44.918
The Bandit ain't nothin'.
He's a mental case.

59:50.215 --> 59:52.342
Good shit!

59:53.427 --> 59:56.096
Banzai!

59:59.933 --> 01:00:02.644
I saw that, you sombitch!

01:00:02.811 --> 01:00:04.897
You did that on purpose!

01:00:05.063 --> 01:00:07.441
You're goin' away till you're grey!

01:00:07.608 --> 01:00:10.152
I got the evidence!
Put the evidence in the car.

01:00:10.319 --> 01:00:14.114
- But, Daddy...
- Put the evidence in the car!

01:00:14.281 --> 01:00:19.369
I'm gonna barbecue
your ass in molasses!

01:00:25.792 --> 01:00:28.504
Put the evidence in the back.

01:00:36.136 --> 01:00:39.890
There's no way, no way...

01:00:40.057 --> 01:00:43.811
that you could come from my loins.

01:00:45.103 --> 01:00:50.526
When I get home, the first thing I'm gonna
do is punch your mama in the mouth.

01:01:00.202 --> 01:01:03.956
I- I'll be with you
in a moment, young man.

01:01:04.122 --> 01:01:08.460
Bandit, honey, this is the Good
Witch of the North speakin'.

01:01:08.627 --> 01:01:11.171
You'd better not come this way.

01:01:11.338 --> 01:01:15.759
There's been a little
fender bender here on 64.

01:01:15.926 --> 01:01:19.471
- Snowman, you copy that?
- Yeah, I got a four on that.

01:01:19.638 --> 01:01:22.349
That'll work for me, 'cause I need to pull off,

01:01:22.516 --> 01:01:25.144
suck up a little go-go juice
and put some groceries down my neck.

01:01:25.310 --> 01:01:26.937
Y'all be careful
and I'll catch ya later.

01:01:27.104 --> 01:01:31.358
- One Snowman. I'm playin' on the side.
- We'll be 10-10 on the side.

01:01:31.525 --> 01:01:35.195
Lady, don't you know
you're supposed to signal?

01:01:35.362 --> 01:01:37.197
Oh? Really?

01:01:47.791 --> 01:01:52.588
<i># They call you the Bandit</i>

01:01:52.754 --> 01:01:57.467
<i># An outlaw untamed</i>

01:01:57.634 --> 01:02:02.306
<i># Shackled only by freedom</i>

01:02:02.681 --> 01:02:05.350
<i># You wear no man's chain</i>

01:02:05.517 --> 01:02:09.855
We got some time.
You wanna stretch your legs, Frog?

01:02:10.022 --> 01:02:12.483
<i># Some say they despise you</i>

01:02:13.484 --> 01:02:18.447
<i># Well, maybe they do</i>

01:02:18.614 --> 01:02:23.118
<i># But deep down inside them</i>

01:02:23.285 --> 01:02:29.666
<i># I bet they wish they were you</i>

01:02:45.265 --> 01:02:46.725
Fill her up, hoss.

01:02:46.892 --> 01:02:50.687
Come on, Frederick.
Come on, boy, my boy.

01:02:50.854 --> 01:02:54.191
Let's go get some
of Lamar's greasy spoon.

01:02:54.358 --> 01:02:58.278
I'm gonna put you
on a diet, Fred. Mercy.

01:03:00.280 --> 01:03:05.327
Come on, Fred. Come on, boy.

01:03:05.494 --> 01:03:07.704
Inside.

01:03:07.871 --> 01:03:10.040
Come on, boy.

01:03:10.207 --> 01:03:13.043
Lamar, surprise.
Look who's here.

01:03:13.210 --> 01:03:15.170
- I knew you was comin'.
- Hi, Snowman.

01:03:15.337 --> 01:03:18.340
What do you mean,
you knew I was comin'?

01:03:25.264 --> 01:03:27.599
Lamar, you're rotten
to the core, you know that.

01:03:27.766 --> 01:03:30.519
About as rotten as that food
you've been poisonin' me with...

01:03:30.686 --> 01:03:34.106
- How many do you want?
- I don't know. Fix the same thing.

01:03:34.273 --> 01:03:36.525
Just cook the onions this time.

01:03:37.442 --> 01:03:41.029
- How have you been, Sugar Bear?
- Pretty good. You, Snowman?

01:03:41.196 --> 01:03:44.074
Oh, pretty good,
considering the shape I'm in.

01:03:44.241 --> 01:03:48.912
Say hello to Waynette.
Looks like old Fred's gettin' fat.

01:03:49.079 --> 01:03:52.666
Yeah, tell me about it. It damn sure
ain't from eatin' the food at this joint.

01:03:52.833 --> 01:03:56.003
- Tell me about that.
- I know it.

01:03:56.170 --> 01:04:00.340
By the way, where did you get
all them warthogs back there?

01:04:00.507 --> 01:04:03.177
Damn if I know. They slid
in here a little while ago.

01:04:03.343 --> 01:04:06.096
I'm gonna slide on out.
Catch you later, Snowman.

01:04:06.263 --> 01:04:09.433
Yeah, why don't you just leave me?

01:04:09.600 --> 01:04:10.976
Yes, operator?

01:04:11.143 --> 01:04:15.063
This is a collect call
from Cledus Snow.

01:04:16.064 --> 01:04:19.610
No, I am not Hank Snow's brother. No.

01:04:22.738 --> 01:04:24.656
Hey, sugarbabe, how you doin'?

01:04:28.494 --> 01:04:31.330
- Could I ask you something?
- Sure.

01:04:33.624 --> 01:04:37.544
Do you think we have
anything in common?

01:04:37.711 --> 01:04:41.715
<i>Besides being chased around
the country in that feckuckteh car?</i>

01:04:41.882 --> 01:04:44.384
Yeah.

01:04:45.093 --> 01:04:47.137
Like what?

01:04:47.304 --> 01:04:50.599
<i>Have you ever seen
the Broadway show Chorus Line?</i>

01:04:50.766 --> 01:04:53.268
No.

01:04:53.435 --> 01:04:56.730
You like Elton John?

01:04:57.189 --> 01:04:58.941
No.

01:05:00.484 --> 01:05:03.862
- Do you know who Casey Tibbs is?
- Baseball player.

01:05:04.029 --> 01:05:08.450
- Close. Richard Petty?
- No.

01:05:08.784 --> 01:05:12.454
- Waylon Jennings? No.
- No.

01:05:14.456 --> 01:05:16.333
When you tell somebody somethin',

01:05:16.500 --> 01:05:19.044
it depends on what part of
the United States you're standin' in...

01:05:19.211 --> 01:05:21.839
as to just how dumb you are.

01:05:26.301 --> 01:05:29.888
Mr Bandit, you have a lyrical way
of cutting through the bullshit.

01:05:30.055 --> 01:05:34.601
And you have a unique way with
the English language, Miss Frog.

01:05:38.021 --> 01:05:42.818
<i># Bandit steals a lady's heart</i>

01:05:42.985 --> 01:05:46.238
<i># With only a smile</i>

01:05:46.864 --> 01:05:50.492
- Don't you take that hat off for anything?
- Sure.

01:05:50.659 --> 01:05:53.829
I take it off for one thing,
and one thing only.

01:05:53.996 --> 01:05:58.750
<i># And you live much too hard</i>

01:05:58.917 --> 01:06:00.794
<i># Bandit, you're the joker</i>

01:06:00.961 --> 01:06:05.299
- If we were lost on a desert island together...
- Yes?

01:06:05.465 --> 01:06:12.264
Do you think we'd get along
and talk and... things?

01:06:13.182 --> 01:06:15.350
Sure.

01:06:15.517 --> 01:06:17.436
Yeah, we'd get along.

01:06:17.603 --> 01:06:23.192
It'd never be boring, I can tell you that.
It would never be boring.

01:06:24.526 --> 01:06:27.946
Take your hat off.

01:06:29.114 --> 01:06:31.909
If you want to.

01:06:32.075 --> 01:06:37.372
<i># They call you the Bandit</i>

01:06:37.539 --> 01:06:40.000
I want to.

01:06:43.212 --> 01:06:48.091
<i># They call you the Bandit</i>

01:06:48.258 --> 01:06:52.596
<i># They call you the Bandit... #</i>

01:07:03.524 --> 01:07:07.569
- No. Honey, we'll be home in a little while.
- Hey!

01:07:08.070 --> 01:07:11.031
Is this your goddamn mutt?

01:07:12.574 --> 01:07:16.245
Honey, I got... I gotta go.
Yeah, I gotta go... Bye.

01:07:17.162 --> 01:07:21.583
- Yeah, that's my dog. Yeah.
- Well, he just bit me.

01:07:21.750 --> 01:07:25.128
- Fred! Come here, Fred.
- I said... He just bit me.

01:07:25.295 --> 01:07:27.840
- Put the son of a bitch out of his misery.
- Let's roast him.

01:07:28.006 --> 01:07:30.801
- That's not a bad idea.
- Eat him.

01:07:30.968 --> 01:07:35.848
I don't think Fred bit you, mister.
Fred absolutely don't like grease.

01:07:41.895 --> 01:07:45.858
Gearjammer, huh?
King of the road, huh?

01:07:51.572 --> 01:07:54.867
- It's time to get out.
- That's a big 10-4.

01:08:45.542 --> 01:08:48.670
How much do I owe you, Billy?

01:08:48.837 --> 01:08:52.758
- 73... 84.
- Never mind, just keep the change.

01:08:52.925 --> 01:08:56.678
Sorry what happened, Snowman.

01:08:57.179 --> 01:09:00.182
It's OK, Lamar.

01:09:27.167 --> 01:09:28.961
Far out.

01:09:34.216 --> 01:09:36.760
What the hell is this,
a drive-in movie?

01:09:40.930 --> 01:09:44.225
Get off of there, you schnauzer's tit!

01:10:04.580 --> 01:10:09.543
- How do, Officer. My name's...
- I don't care if it's Broderick Crawford.

01:10:09.710 --> 01:10:13.839
Don't you know you can't drive
a piece of shit like that on the highway?

01:10:14.006 --> 01:10:17.676
I'll thank you not to use
that kind of language in my presence.

01:10:17.843 --> 01:10:21.722
Never mind that crap.
What the hell is this?

01:10:22.764 --> 01:10:25.684
- This is evidence.
- Evidence?

01:10:25.851 --> 01:10:30.981
I don't care what it is. You can't drive
this piece of shit on my highway.

01:10:31.148 --> 01:10:33.901
I'm tellin' you for the last time.

01:10:34.067 --> 01:10:38.864
I have my young son in the car,
and I don't wanna hear that kinda language.

01:10:39.031 --> 01:10:44.119
- Look! I'm askin' you one single, goddamn...
