01:19:10.334 --> 01:19:13.170
<i># I'm eastbound
Just watch ol' Bandit run #</i>

01:19:13.337 --> 01:19:18.425
I don't care if you're the Governor of Texas.
You're makin' a big mistake.

01:19:22.596 --> 01:19:25.682
Read him his rights, Junior.

01:19:25.849 --> 01:19:27.643
You have the right to remain silent.

01:19:27.810 --> 01:19:31.855
Anything you say may be held
against you in a court of law. And...

01:19:32.022 --> 01:19:34.441
What's all this about?

01:19:34.691 --> 01:19:38.862
Oh, hello, Officer!
Glad you're here to assist me.

01:19:39.029 --> 01:19:41.698
My name is Sheriff Buford T. Justice.

01:19:41.865 --> 01:19:44.952
I have just apprehended the Bandit.

01:19:45.118 --> 01:19:48.539
No, sir. You just apprehended my captain.

01:19:52.251 --> 01:19:55.003
- Take the cuffs off, Junior.
- But, Daddy, we just...

01:19:55.170 --> 01:19:58.841
Take the cuffs off, you moose twit.

01:20:04.138 --> 01:20:10.102
May I express my feelings
about inconveniencing you...

01:20:10.269 --> 01:20:13.522
But if you gonna hang out
in these kinda joints...

01:20:13.689 --> 01:20:16.692
wear a badge on your didie.

01:20:37.087 --> 01:20:39.548
Oh, no.

01:20:39.715 --> 01:20:42.009
Hey, Bandit. Listen to this.

01:20:43.594 --> 01:20:46.513
<i>You know who that is?
That's Mr Evel Knievel.</i>

01:20:46.680 --> 01:20:49.141
He snuck in my back door
when I wasn't lookin'.

01:20:49.308 --> 01:20:52.311
Give me a hand, or we gonna be
in a heap of trouble.

01:20:52.478 --> 01:20:56.773
<i>- Please roger that transmission.
- Hold on to Fred. Here comes the cavalry.</i>

01:21:08.952 --> 01:21:10.913
- Howdy, Officer.
- How ya doin'?

01:21:11.079 --> 01:21:17.044
Give me your licence and manifest, boy.
You know you was goin' 96 miles an hour?

01:21:17.211 --> 01:21:19.505
- I was doin' 96...
- You're damn right, you was.

01:21:19.671 --> 01:21:21.798
I didn't know this truck could do 96.

01:21:21.965 --> 01:21:25.761
The judge gets to you, he's gonna
turn you every way but loose.

01:21:25.928 --> 01:21:29.556
It's time you truckers learn
these roads don't belong to you.

01:21:37.648 --> 01:21:40.984
You be careful, you hear?

01:22:00.712 --> 01:22:05.342
<i>- Whoa. Want a little piece of advice, Bandit?
- Yeah. Lay it on me, son.</i>

01:22:05.509 --> 01:22:10.764
Don't take your foot off of that hammer.
Them bears'll pour over you like maple syrup.

01:22:46.842 --> 01:22:48.635
- You all right?
- Yeah.

01:22:48.802 --> 01:22:53.265
- Don't you know this ain't Saturday?
- Thanks a lot.

01:23:27.591 --> 01:23:30.803
We don't need assistance.
I've got him in my sights.

01:23:37.392 --> 01:23:40.813
Headquarters, disregard
my last transmission.

01:24:10.134 --> 01:24:14.471
Son... you reckon you can
let me off at the next exit?

01:24:15.389 --> 01:24:17.641
- Go get your daddy a beer.
- OK.

01:24:17.808 --> 01:24:20.227
<i>...I understand every cop
in the state's after him.</i>

01:24:20.394 --> 01:24:24.273
- Stay 10-10. I'll let you know.
- That's a big 10-4.

01:24:24.439 --> 01:24:27.192
Damn, he's been stirring up some trouble.

01:24:36.118 --> 01:24:38.829
Ooh, it's the Bandit!

01:24:54.803 --> 01:24:59.766
<i>I'm Hot To Trot. Just tell me how
I can help and I'm with ya, body and soul.</i>

01:24:59.933 --> 01:25:03.228
<i>- Channel clear.
- Breaker one-nine, breaker one-nine.</i>

01:25:03.395 --> 01:25:05.647
Is that Hot Pants Hilliard
yakkin' out there?

01:25:05.814 --> 01:25:08.817
<i>- And who wants to know?
- This is the Bandit, darling.</i>

01:25:08.984 --> 01:25:12.654
Well, where are you,
you bodied-up, smooth-talkin' thing?

01:25:12.821 --> 01:25:15.032
And how can I help?
Bring it back.

01:25:15.199 --> 01:25:18.118
You still workin' at that
choke-and-puke on West 85?

01:25:18.285 --> 01:25:21.830
Affirmative, affirmative.
I'm still dishin' it out.

01:25:22.372 --> 01:25:27.044
We'll come screamin' by in five minutes
with a herd of smokeys on our ass.

01:25:27.669 --> 01:25:30.297
<i>How 'bout gettin' those pallies
of yours out there, block 'em off?</i>

01:25:30.464 --> 01:25:33.467
Love to! But hey,
you're gonna owe me one.

01:25:33.634 --> 01:25:37.346
- I owe you a big one.
- That's a big 10-4.

01:25:37.513 --> 01:25:39.181
10-4.

01:25:41.016 --> 01:25:45.229
All right, gang, we're gonna go
for a big smokey red 22. Wahoo!

01:25:45.395 --> 01:25:47.189
- Ride with me?
- Yeah.

01:25:52.986 --> 01:25:58.158
- You sure we ain't gonna get in trouble?
- Nah. I've done it before.

01:26:12.881 --> 01:26:16.844
- We're comin' at you, darlin'. Are you ready?
- Ready, willin' and able.

01:26:17.010 --> 01:26:21.098
"Ready and willing. " Ha.
She always was.

01:26:24.351 --> 01:26:27.938
<i>OK, gang, be alert,
'cause here he comes.</i>

01:26:28.105 --> 01:26:32.693
<i>- Well, go ahead and answer.
- 10-4, Hot Pants. We copy.</i>

01:26:32.860 --> 01:26:34.820
Let go of the button.

01:27:17.321 --> 01:27:21.533
Paydirt. I just picked up
the Bandit eastbound on 95.

01:27:21.700 --> 01:27:23.285
All units converge.

01:27:23.452 --> 01:27:26.914
<i>I copy, Chopper One.
I'm on my way.</i>

01:27:39.968 --> 01:27:41.178
<i>Heading for the fairgrounds!</i>

01:28:05.244 --> 01:28:09.248
<i>This is car 12, Bobby Lee,
and I have him westbound on 75.</i>

01:28:21.343 --> 01:28:26.473
<i>- Cledus, where the hell are we?
- Four miles to go, good buddy.</i>

01:28:27.975 --> 01:28:31.895
- Four miles. Goddamn it!
- Four miles...

01:28:38.026 --> 01:28:41.572
Bo, did you count on this?

01:28:41.738 --> 01:28:44.449
I mean, all of this?

01:28:49.454 --> 01:28:52.374
No, I didn't, honey.

01:28:56.545 --> 01:28:59.965
<i>- Cledus?
- Talk to me, my boy.</i>

01:29:00.132 --> 01:29:03.677
Goddamn it, son,
we gave it our best shot.

01:29:03.844 --> 01:29:07.890
I don't like this any more
than you do, but...

01:29:08.056 --> 01:29:11.185
We ain't gonna make it, son.
We're gonna hang it up.

01:29:11.351 --> 01:29:13.937
Whoa, negatory, negatory!
You crazy or somethin'?

01:29:14.104 --> 01:29:18.650
We come this far, ain't we? When we say
we gonna do a job, we do a job!

01:29:18.817 --> 01:29:21.820
It's me they're after. They don't
even know Cledus Snow exists.

01:29:21.987 --> 01:29:26.950
Oh, they don't?
Well, I'll tell you what we gonna do.

01:29:27.784 --> 01:29:31.121
We gonna introduce 'em to the boy.
So move over, good buddy,

01:29:31.288 --> 01:29:36.210
'cause the Snowman is comin' through.
Hold on to your ass, Fred.

01:29:45.761 --> 01:29:47.721
Hot damn, we're gonna make it.

01:30:06.365 --> 01:30:09.201
Move them vehicles.
We gotta get through!

01:30:09.368 --> 01:30:11.787
Here they come!

01:30:49.116 --> 01:30:52.828
Daddy, you're about to have
your evenin' ruined for you.

01:31:07.634 --> 01:31:09.678
- OK.
- All right.

01:31:09.845 --> 01:31:12.681
- We're in trouble.
- I know we're in trouble.

01:31:12.848 --> 01:31:14.850
- What time is it?
- One minute after.

01:31:15.017 --> 01:31:17.936
- Goddamn, we're 10 minutes early.
- We're in trouble!

01:31:18.103 --> 01:31:20.731
We need a way out of here.
We need the money.

01:31:20.898 --> 01:31:24.276
Here's my Cadillac. That'll leave me
with an even dozen. Good luck, son.

01:31:24.443 --> 01:31:26.320
- Cledus, get the money.
- How 'bout the money?

01:31:26.487 --> 01:31:28.864
- How 'bout double or nothin'?
- How 'bout forgettin' it?

01:31:29.031 --> 01:31:30.574
What about double or nothin'?

01:31:30.741 --> 01:31:34.119
You run up to Boston,
bring back some clam chowder.

01:31:35.454 --> 01:31:37.206
- You're on.
- Uh, you're on.

01:31:37.372 --> 01:31:41.168
- In 18 hours?
- You're still on.

01:31:41.335 --> 01:31:45.088
Y- y-you're crazy!
And I'm divorced!

01:31:45.255 --> 01:31:48.759
And you... Ain't half bad, is it?

01:32:06.568 --> 01:32:10.697
20 to one
I break the son of a bitch this time.

01:32:16.036 --> 01:32:18.121
Gimme 500 on the Bandit.

01:32:25.045 --> 01:32:28.382
Apprehend that horse ass
for reckless drivin'!

01:32:28.549 --> 01:32:33.470
- But, Daddy, he's...
- Do what I tell you, you pile of monkey nuts!

01:32:39.268 --> 01:32:43.730
<i>Sheriff Buford T. Justice, please.</i>

01:32:43.897 --> 01:32:46.775
- Who there?
- This is Bandit Darville talkin'.

01:32:47.526 --> 01:32:49.736
Where are you, you sombitch?

01:32:49.945 --> 01:32:53.949
Before I tell you where I am, Sheriff,
there's just one thing I wanna say.

01:32:54.116 --> 01:32:58.370
You must be part coon dog,
'cause I been chased by the best of 'em,

01:32:58.537 --> 01:33:02.291
and son, you make 'em look
like they're all runnin' in slow motion.

01:33:02.457 --> 01:33:06.879
- I just wanna say that.
